# primes-project
#### A project to find, list and study primes


# Benchmark on MacBook Pro with Apple M2 Chip
#### Prove mersenne numbers on prime:
```
$ time ./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^5-1" 5
31 is prime.
./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^5-1" 5  0,00s user 0,01s system 61% cpu 0,016 total

### approx. 5000 decimals
$ time ./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^16653-1" 20
 is composite.
./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^16653-1" 20  2,34s user 0,01s system 99% cpu 2,357 total

### approx 10000 decimals
$ time ./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^33219-1" 5
 is composite.
./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^33219-1" 5  12,75s user 0,02s system 99% cpu 12,779 total

### approx. 20000 decimals
$ time ./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^66431-1" 5
 is composite.
./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^66431-1" 5  66,69s user 0,10s system 99% cpu 1:06,79 total

### approx. 30000 decimals
$ time ./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^99647-1" 5
 is composite.
./miller_rabin_mersenne "1*2^99647-1" 5  174,39s user 0,27s system 99% cpu 2:54,66 total
```
